{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"I'm a journalist,"},{"time":2115,"text":"so I like to look for the untold stories,"},{"time":4690,"text":"the lives that quietly play out\nunder the scream of headlines."},{"time":8977,"text":"I've also been going about the business\nof putting down roots,"},{"time":12458,"text":"choosing a partner, making babies."},{"time":15206,"text":"So for the last few years,"},{"time":17461,"text":"I've been trying to understand"},{"time":18948,"text":"what constitutes\nthe 21st-century good life,"},{"time":23085,"text":"both because I'm fascinated by the moral\nand philosophical implications,"},{"time":27719,"text":"but also because I'm in desperate\nneed of answers myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31641,"text":"We live in tenuous times."},{"time":34402,"text":"In fact, for the first time\nin American history,"},{"time":37611,"text":"the majority of parents do not think\nthat their kids will be better off"},{"time":41755,"text":"than they were."},{"time":43211,"text":"This is true of rich and poor,\nmen and women."},{"time":47000,"text":"Now, some of you\nmight hear this and feel sad."},{"time":49589,"text":"After all, America is deeply invested"},{"time":52605,"text":"in this idea of economic transcendence,"},{"time":55508,"text":"that every generation kind of\nleapfrogs the one before it,"},{"time":59092,"text":"earning more, buying more, being more."},{"time":63299,"text":"We've exported this dream\nall over the world,"},{"time":65481,"text":"so kids in Brazil and China and even Kenya"},{"time":68414,"text":"inherit our insatiable expectation"},{"time":71195,"text":"for more."},{"time":73063,"text":"But when I read this historic poll\nfor the first time,"},{"time":76144,"text":"it didn't actually make me feel sad."},{"time":78593,"text":"It felt like a provocation."},{"time":81181,"text":"\"Better off\" -- based on whose standards?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85030,"text":"Is \"better off\" finding a secure job"},{"time":87137,"text":"that you can count on\nfor the rest of your life?"},{"time":90027,"text":"Those are nearly extinct."},{"time":91788,"text":"People move jobs, on average,\nevery 4.7 years,"},{"time":95809,"text":"and it's estimated that by 2020,"},{"time":97794,"text":"nearly half of Americans\nwill be freelancers."},{"time":101523,"text":"OK, so is better off just a number?"},{"time":104498,"text":"Is it about earning\nas much as you possibly can?"},{"time":108060,"text":"By that singular measurement,\nwe are failing."},{"time":111316,"text":"Median per capita income\nhas been flat since about 2000,"},{"time":115537,"text":"adjusted for inflation."},{"time":118005,"text":"All right, so is better off getting\na big house with a white picket fence?"},{"time":122710,"text":"Less of us are doing that."},{"time":124718,"text":"Nearly five million people lost\ntheir homes in the Great Recession,"},{"time":128398,"text":"and even more of us sobered up\nabout the lengths we were willing to go --"},{"time":132796,"text":"or be tricked into going,\nin many predatory cases --"},{"time":135567,"text":"to hold that deed."},{"time":137575,"text":"Home-ownership rates\nare at their lowest since 1995."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142117,"text":"All right, so we're not\nfinding steady employment,"},{"time":145489,"text":"we're not earning as much money,"},{"time":147246,"text":"and we're not living in big fancy houses."},{"time":150372,"text":"Toll the funeral bells"},{"time":152111,"text":"for everything that made America great."},{"time":156147,"text":"But,"},{"time":157767,"text":"are those the best measurements\nof a country's greatness,"},{"time":161697,"text":"of a life well lived?"},{"time":163870,"text":"What I think makes America great\nis its spirit of reinvention."},{"time":168034,"text":"In the wake of the Great Recession,"},{"time":169776,"text":"more and more Americans are redefining\nwhat \"better off\" really means."},{"time":174412,"text":"Turns out, it has more to do\nwith community and creativity"},{"time":178422,"text":"than dollars and cents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180917,"text":"Now, let me be very clear:"},{"time":183480,"text":"the 14.8 percent of Americans\nliving in poverty need money,"},{"time":188697,"text":"plain and simple."},{"time":190101,"text":"And all of us need policies\nthat protect us from exploitation"},{"time":193786,"text":"by employers and financial institutions."},{"time":197011,"text":"Nothing that follows is meant to suggest\nthat the gap between rich and poor"},{"time":201686,"text":"is anything but profoundly immoral."},{"time":206224,"text":"But,"},{"time":207553,"text":"too often we let\nthe conversation stop there."},{"time":210804,"text":"We talk about poverty as if\nit were a monolithic experience;"},{"time":214553,"text":"about the poor as if\nthey were solely victims."},{"time":218126,"text":"Part of what I've learned\nin my research and reporting"},{"time":221007,"text":"is that the art of living well"},{"time":223437,"text":"is often practiced most masterfully"},{"time":226449,"text":"by the most vulnerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230253,"text":"Now, if necessity\nis the mother of invention,"},{"time":232769,"text":"I've come to believe"},{"time":234491,"text":"that recession can be\nthe father of consciousness."},{"time":238879,"text":"It confronts us with profound questions,"},{"time":241741,"text":"questions we might be too lazy\nor distracted to ask"},{"time":244908,"text":"in times of relative comfort."},{"time":247047,"text":"How should we work?"},{"time":248634,"text":"How should we live?"},{"time":250766,"text":"All of us, whether we realize it or not,"},{"time":253029,"text":"seek answers to these questions,"},{"time":254625,"text":"with our ancestors\nkind of whispering in our ears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259020,"text":"My great-grandfather\nwas a drunk in Detroit,"},{"time":263167,"text":"who sometimes managed\nto hold down a factory job."},{"time":266611,"text":"He had, as unbelievable as it might sound,"},{"time":269551,"text":"21 children,"},{"time":271446,"text":"with one woman, my great-grandmother,"},{"time":273852,"text":"who died at 47 years old\nof ovarian cancer."},{"time":277945,"text":"Now, I'm pregnant with my second child,"},{"time":279904,"text":"and I cannot even fathom\nwhat she must have gone through."},{"time":284502,"text":"And if you're trying to do the math --\nthere were six sets of twins."},{"time":288810,"text":"So my grandfather, their son,"},{"time":291572,"text":"became a traveling salesman,"},{"time":293295,"text":"and he lived boom and bust."},{"time":294814,"text":"So my dad grew up answering\nthe door for debt collectors"},{"time":298524,"text":"and pretending his parents weren't home."},{"time":300979,"text":"He actually took his braces off himself\nwith pliers in the garage,"},{"time":305183,"text":"when his father admitted\nhe didn't have money"},{"time":307366,"text":"to go back to the orthodontist."},{"time":309778,"text":"So my dad, unsurprisingly,"},{"time":312573,"text":"became a bankruptcy lawyer."},{"time":314665,"text":"Couldn't write this in a novel, right?"},{"time":317236,"text":"He was obsessed with providing\na secure foundation"},{"time":320541,"text":"for my brother and I."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322521,"text":"So I ask these questions\nby way of a few generations of struggle."},{"time":326895,"text":"My parents made sure that I grew up\non a kind of steady ground"},{"time":329976,"text":"that allows one to question\nand risk and leap."},{"time":333909,"text":"And ironically, and probably\nsometimes to their frustration,"},{"time":337247,"text":"it is their steadfast\ncommitment to security"},{"time":340555,"text":"that allows me to question its value,"},{"time":343044,"text":"or at least its value\nas we've historically defined it"},{"time":346046,"text":"in the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348870,"text":"So let's dig into this first question:"},{"time":351267,"text":"How should we work?"},{"time":354397,"text":"We should work like our mothers."},{"time":357754,"text":"That's right -- we've spent decades"},{"time":359917,"text":"trying to fit women into a work world\nbuilt for company men."},{"time":364358,"text":"And many have done backbends to fit in,"},{"time":366272,"text":"but others have carved\na more unconventional path,"},{"time":369652,"text":"creating a patchwork of meaning and money"},{"time":371875,"text":"with enough flexibility\nto do what they need to do"},{"time":374620,"text":"for those that they love."},{"time":376993,"text":"My mom called it \"just making it work.\""},{"time":379574,"text":"Today I hear life coaches\ncall it \"a portfolio career.\""},{"time":383956,"text":"Whatever you call it,"},{"time":385639,"text":"more and more men are craving\nthese whole, if not harried, lives."},{"time":391332,"text":"They're waking up to their desire\nand duty to be present fathers and sons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396547,"text":"Now, artist Ann Hamilton has said,"},{"time":399008,"text":"\"Labor is a way of knowing.\""},{"time":402458,"text":"Labor is a way of knowing."},{"time":403770,"text":"In other words, what we work on"},{"time":405802,"text":"is what we understand about the world."},{"time":409043,"text":"If this is true, and I think it is,"},{"time":411266,"text":"then women who have disproportionately\ncared for the little ones"},{"time":414862,"text":"and the sick ones and the aging ones,"},{"time":416863,"text":"have disproportionately benefited"},{"time":419819,"text":"from the most profound kind\nof knowing there is:"},{"time":423373,"text":"knowing the human condition."},{"time":426442,"text":"By prioritizing care,"},{"time":428618,"text":"men are, in a sense, staking their claim"},{"time":431218,"text":"to the full range of human existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435097,"text":"Now, this means the nine-to-five\nno longer works for anyone."},{"time":438685,"text":"Punch clocks are becoming obsolete,\nas are career ladders."},{"time":441535,"text":"Whole industries are being born\nand dying every day."},{"time":444627,"text":"It's all nonlinear from here."},{"time":447090,"text":"So we need to stop asking kids,"},{"time":449126,"text":"\"What do you want to be when you grow up?\""},{"time":451206,"text":"and start asking them,\n\"How do you want to be when you grow up?\""},{"time":455247,"text":"Their work will constantly change."},{"time":457170,"text":"The common denominator is them."},{"time":459504,"text":"So the more they understand their gifts"},{"time":461469,"text":"and create crews of ideal collaborators,"},{"time":463948,"text":"the better off they will be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466717,"text":"The challenge ahead is to reinvent\nthe social safety net"},{"time":469404,"text":"to fit this increasingly\nfragmented economy."},{"time":472365,"text":"We need portable health benefits."},{"time":474248,"text":"We need policies that reflect\nthat everyone deserves to be vulnerable"},{"time":477881,"text":"or care for vulnerable others,"},{"time":479403,"text":"without becoming destitute."},{"time":481035,"text":"We need to seriously consider\na universal basic income."},{"time":483707,"text":"We need to reinvent labor organizing."},{"time":486682,"text":"The promise of a work world\nthat is structured to actually fit"},{"time":490572,"text":"our 21st century values,"},{"time":492496,"text":"not some archaic idea\nabout bringing home the bacon,"},{"time":495457,"text":"is long overdue --"},{"time":497671,"text":"just ask your mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499877,"text":"Now, how about the second question:"},{"time":501603,"text":"How should we live?"},{"time":503737,"text":"We should live"},{"time":505507,"text":"like our immigrant ancestors."},{"time":509174,"text":"When they came to America,"},{"time":510635,"text":"they often shared apartments,\nsurvival tactics, child care --"},{"time":514889,"text":"always knew how to fill one more belly,"},{"time":516919,"text":"no matter how small the food available."},{"time":519770,"text":"But they were told that success meant\nleaving the village behind"},{"time":523360,"text":"and pursuing that iconic symbol\nof the American Dream,"},{"time":526436,"text":"the white picket fence."},{"time":528460,"text":"And even today,\nwe see a white picket fence"},{"time":530508,"text":"and we think success, self-possession."},{"time":532905,"text":"But when you strip away\nthe sentimentality,"},{"time":535160,"text":"what it really does is divides us."},{"time":538140,"text":"Many Americans are rejecting\nthe white picket fence"},{"time":540737,"text":"and the kind of highly privatized life\nthat happened within it,"},{"time":544076,"text":"and reclaiming village life,"},{"time":545890,"text":"reclaiming interdependence instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549311,"text":"Fifty million of us, for example,"},{"time":550938,"text":"live in intergenerational households."},{"time":554018,"text":"This number exploded\nwith the Great Recession,"},{"time":556770,"text":"but it turns out people\nactually like living this way."},{"time":559432,"text":"Two-thirds of those who are living\nwith multiple generations under one roof"},{"time":563304,"text":"say it's improved their relationships."},{"time":566145,"text":"Some people are choosing\nto share homes not with family,"},{"time":568993,"text":"but with other people who understand\nthe health and economic benefits"},{"time":572377,"text":"of daily community."},{"time":574082,"text":"CoAbode, an online platform\nfor single moms looking to share homes"},{"time":577740,"text":"with other single moms,"},{"time":579127,"text":"has 50,000 users."},{"time":581761,"text":"And people over 65 are especially prone"},{"time":584422,"text":"to be looking for these alternative\nliving arrangements."},{"time":588074,"text":"They understand that their quality of life"},{"time":590597,"text":"depends on a mix\nof solitude and solidarity."},{"time":595727,"text":"Which is true of all of us\nwhen you think about it,"},{"time":598244,"text":"young and old alike."},{"time":599632,"text":"For too long, we've pretended\nthat happiness is a king in his castle."},{"time":604306,"text":"But all the research proves otherwise."},{"time":607006,"text":"It shows that the healthiest,\nhappiest and even safest --"},{"time":610033,"text":"in terms of both climate change disaster,\nin terms of crime, all of that --"},{"time":616131,"text":"are Americans who live lives\nintertwined with their neighbors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620661,"text":"Now, I've experienced this firsthand."},{"time":623076,"text":"For the last few years, I've been living\nin a cohousing community."},{"time":626292,"text":"It's 1.5 acres of persimmon trees,"},{"time":629925,"text":"this prolific blackberry bush\nthat snakes around a community garden,"},{"time":633701,"text":"all smack-dab, by the way,\nin the middle of urban Oakland."},{"time":637447,"text":"The nine units are all built\nto be different,"},{"time":639590,"text":"different sizes, different shapes,"},{"time":641263,"text":"but they're meant to be\nas green as possible."},{"time":643401,"text":"So big, shiny black\nsolar cells on our roof"},{"time":645568,"text":"mean our electricity bill rarely exceeds"},{"time":647526,"text":"more than five bucks in a month."},{"time":649787,"text":"The 25 of us who live there are all\ndifferent ages and political persuasions"},{"time":653622,"text":"and professions,"},{"time":654804,"text":"and we live in homes that have everything\na typical home would have."},{"time":658106,"text":"But additionally,"},{"time":659284,"text":"we share an industrial-sized\nkitchen and eating area,"},{"time":661824,"text":"where we have common meals twice a week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663913,"text":"Now, people, when I tell them\nI live like this,"},{"time":666176,"text":"often have one of two extreme reactions."},{"time":668106,"text":"Either they say, \"Why doesn't\neveryone live like this?\""},{"time":670779,"text":"Or they say, \"That sounds\ntotally horrifying."},{"time":673531,"text":"I would never want to do that.\""},{"time":675054,"text":"So let me reassure you: there is\na sacred respect for privacy among us,"},{"time":680614,"text":"but also a commitment to what we call\n\"radical hospitality\" --"},{"time":685535,"text":"not the kind advertised\nby the Four Seasons,"},{"time":688704,"text":"but the kind that says that every\nsingle person is worthy of kindness,"},{"time":694355,"text":"full stop, end of sentence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697129,"text":"The biggest surprise for me\nof living in a community like this?"},{"time":701335,"text":"You share all the domestic labor --\nthe repairing, the cooking, the weeding --"},{"time":705110,"text":"but you also share the emotional labor."},{"time":707573,"text":"Rather than depending only\non the idealized family unit"},{"time":710620,"text":"to get all of your emotional needs met,"},{"time":712512,"text":"you have two dozen other people\nthat you can go to"},{"time":714945,"text":"to talk about a hard day at work"},{"time":716805,"text":"or troubleshoot how to handle\nan abusive teacher."},{"time":720038,"text":"Teenagers in our community will often go\nto an adult that is not their parent"},{"time":725626,"text":"to ask for advice."},{"time":727310,"text":"It's what bell hooks\ncalled \"revolutionary parenting,\""},{"time":730853,"text":"this humble acknowledgment"},{"time":732675,"text":"that kids are healthier when they have\na wider range of adults"},{"time":735795,"text":"to emulate and count on."},{"time":738451,"text":"Turns out, adults are healthier, too."},{"time":741568,"text":"It's a lot of pressure,"},{"time":743180,"text":"trying to be that perfect family\nbehind that white picket fence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748290,"text":"The \"new better off,\"\nas I've come to call it,"},{"time":750658,"text":"is less about investing\nin the perfect family"},{"time":753638,"text":"and more about investing\nin the imperfect village,"},{"time":757147,"text":"whether that's relatives\nliving under one roof,"},{"time":759397,"text":"a cohousing community like mine,"},{"time":761261,"text":"or just a bunch of neighbors\nwho pledge to really know"},{"time":764215,"text":"and look out for one another."},{"time":766134,"text":"It's good common sense, right?"},{"time":768466,"text":"And yet, money has often made us dumb"},{"time":771297,"text":"about reaching out."},{"time":773575,"text":"The most reliable wealth"},{"time":775632,"text":"is found in relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779511,"text":"The new better off is not\nan individual prospect at all."},{"time":783384,"text":"In fact, if you're a failure\nor you think you're a failure,"},{"time":786477,"text":"I've got some good news for you:"},{"time":788112,"text":"you might be a success by standards\nyou have not yet honored."},{"time":792404,"text":"Maybe you're a mediocre earner\nbut a masterful father."},{"time":796477,"text":"Maybe you can't afford your dream home,"},{"time":798383,"text":"but you throw legendary\nneighborhood parties."},{"time":802462,"text":"If you're a textbook success,"},{"time":804250,"text":"the implications of what I'm saying\ncould be more grim for you."},{"time":808344,"text":"You might be a failure\nby standards you hold dear"},{"time":811709,"text":"but that the world doesn't reward."},{"time":814719,"text":"Only you can know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817310,"text":"I know that I am not a tribute"},{"time":820550,"text":"to my great-grandmother,"},{"time":822060,"text":"who lived such a short and brutish life,"},{"time":824753,"text":"if I earn enough money to afford\nevery creature comfort."},{"time":828614,"text":"You can't buy your way\nout of suffering or into meaning."},{"time":831767,"text":"There is no home big enough"},{"time":833525,"text":"to erase the pain\nthat she must have endured."},{"time":837435,"text":"I am a tribute to her"},{"time":838709,"text":"if I live a life as connected\nand courageous as possible."},{"time":844256,"text":"In the midst of such\nwidespread uncertainty,"},{"time":847281,"text":"we may, in fact, be insecure."},{"time":850334,"text":"But we can let that insecurity\nmake us brittle"},{"time":853216,"text":"or supple."},{"time":854859,"text":"We can turn inward, lose faith\nin the power of institutions to change --"},{"time":859890,"text":"even lose faith in ourselves."},{"time":862332,"text":"Or we can turn outward,"},{"time":864300,"text":"cultivate faith in our ability\nto reach out, to connect, to create."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871063,"text":"Turns out, the biggest danger"},{"time":874020,"text":"is not failing to achieve\nthe American Dream."},{"time":877624,"text":"The biggest danger is achieving a dream"},{"time":880086,"text":"that you don't actually believe in."},{"time":883362,"text":"So don't do that."},{"time":885046,"text":"Do the harder, more interesting thing,"},{"time":887712,"text":"which is to compose a life\nwhere what you do every single day,"},{"time":891784,"text":"the people you give your best love\nand ingenuity and energy to,"},{"time":895486,"text":"aligns as closely as possible\nwith what you believe."},{"time":899010,"text":"That, not something as mundane\nas making money,"},{"time":902439,"text":"is a tribute to your ancestors."},{"time":904432,"text":"That is the beautiful struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908861,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910076,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}